# React Component Patterns

## Use Shared Components

Always use existing shared components from `@/components/shared/`:

| Component | Use For |
|-----------|---------|
| `Button` | All buttons (variants: primary, secondary, destructive, ghost) |
| `Modal` | All modals (sizes: sm, md, lg, xl, full) |
| `ConfirmationDialog` | Destructive action confirmations |
| `DropdownSelect` | Select inputs |
| `Form` | Form layouts |
| `Overlay` | Floating panels |

```tsx
import { Button, Modal } from '@/components/shared';
```

## Styling with CSS Variables

Use `scripture-*` CSS variables for theming (supports dark mode):

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - uses theme variables
<div className="bg-scripture-surface text-scripture-text border-scripture-border">
<button className="bg-scripture-accent text-scripture-bg hover:bg-scripture-accent/90">

// ❌ Wrong - hardcoded colors won't respect theme
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900">
```

**Key variables**: `scripture-bg`, `scripture-surface`, `scripture-elevated`, `scripture-text`, `scripture-muted`, `scripture-accent`, `scripture-border`, `scripture-error`

## Component Structure

```tsx
/**
 * Component Name
 * 
 * What this component does.
 */

import { useState } from 'react';
import { Button } from '@/components/shared';
import { useXxxStore } from '@/stores/xxxStore';
import type { SomeType } from '@/types/...';

interface ComponentProps {
  /** Description of prop */
  requiredProp: string;
  /** Optional with default */
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
}

export function ComponentName({ requiredProp, size = 'md' }: ComponentProps) {
  // ...
}
```

## Conventions

- **Named exports**: `export function Foo()` (not default exports)
- **Barrel exports**: Each feature folder has `index.ts` re-exporting components
- **Props interface**: JSDoc comment on each prop
- **UI text font**: Use `font-ui` class for UI labels/buttons
- **Focus states**: Include `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-scripture-accent` for interactive elements
- **Transitions**: Use `transition-colors` for hover states
